n=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> Raid organisers ask for as much CR/FR and MR as possible.<br>
<br>
What do you guys wear to a dragon raid and what CR/FR and MR do you get from it all?<br>
<br>
The old &quot;I go for AC&quot; excuse don't count vs Dragons: their fear renders you useless to your party, and their breath does as much damage as their claws do. <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/mastersofavalon" target="_blank">Masters of Avalon</a><br>
Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uatwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AtWork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 8:47:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> Well, to be honest, I don't worry about the stuff I wear on dragon raids.  My gear usually has me in the low 30s for everything but MR which runs low 40s.  By the time a bard gets the normal resists spells thrown on them by casters; and starts twisting Elemental and Guardian, my resists easily climb to or above 200.  Other classes have to worry about it more than bards because we generate our our resists.  The other classes don't always have the benefit of a bard in their group, so they have to really work on the gear side.<br>
<br>
Just what I've found from experience.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion<br>
Bardette <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uaerian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerian</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>El Jugador de Brell</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 9:54:23 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/slackerz_r_us/Eljugador.jpg height=215 width =115></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> the key from what i noticed when i grouped with a bard on dragon raids(as Aerian seeing Kat hasnt been on any yet)... if you get around 50+ unbuffed then have your resist fire and GRM you get to 100 with those... THEN you got teh bard song which give ya lots of resist...<br>
<br>
my idea with Kat when i go... is to give him enough  MR / FR equip to be 50 at least unbuffed... prolly 70 or so unbuffed seeing his MR is currently 50 without anything special.. with it at 70 FR/CR and 70MR you add the buffs thats 115FR/CR(with druid circle spells) and 120MR... then you throw in bard songs and its way up there so you should be doing quite well versus the AE fear and AE lava/ice<br>
<br>
even with just 110FR/CR and 120MR Aerian was able to resist fire/ice and all the fears at 48-54without problems... bards shouldnt have to worry about throwing on TOO much extra gear seeing that their songs make up for alot of gear that others would need...its good to have it but it doesnt seem as necessary imo...<br>
<br>
/shrug... i just know ill have 70ish base for fr/cr/mr <br>
<br>
 <p><p align=center><font color=blue><b><i><font size=5>Katran Eljugador</b></font><br>
<font color=orange>"The Player"<br>
40th Bard<br>
Norrathian Social Club</i></font><br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>"Running out of ways to run... I can't see, I can't be... Over and over and under my skin...All this attention is doing me in!" - Slipknot - "Surfacing"</p></font>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 4:18:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> bards song is very important to the rest of the group (mostly tanks if set up right) and the tanks GOTTA stay alive to keep the aggro and do 50% of the dmg, as a bard i recommend having at least 70+ unbuffed resists<br>
<br>
Quemn Wyndrunner<br>
52 Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/7/00 5:55:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
<br>
If the bard is giving huge resistance buffs to the tanks, (s)he has to make sure his/her resistances are as high as possible. A feared or dead bard is no bloody use to a tank group.<br>
<br>
That's why I'm even in the process of getting those lambent quest armour pieces for the odd +5 MR or +3 FR from Icy Greaves, Fiery Vambraces or Firewalker Boots etc.<br>
<br>
C'mon mithril bards (you know who you are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) what are you wearing that doesn't show, that compensates for what does show (...and why am I stepping over your bodies in the Dragon's Lair..)? <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/mastersofavalon" target="_blank">Masters of Avalon</a><br>
Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukalsyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalsyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/17/00 6:45:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> Actually I disagree a bit.  I used to substitute my gear like most people on a dragon raid to get as high as possible resists.  But I dont think its critical either way.  I do think having a high resist is more important then high AC.  Its only rarely a Dragon will attack a Bard with so many taunting tanks and nukers doing as much damage as possible.  The breath is AE so it will effect you every time.<br>
<br>
However, I dont think a bard should just abandon AC either to try and Max out resists.  Often times your not just giving up AC for resists.  You may be giving up Stats or added HPS as well.  And dont forget the all important fashion statement.<br>
<br>
It really comes down to a judgement call.  Where do you stand naturally with resists using just your regular everyday gear?  What kind of buffs will be cast on you pre-dragon rush?  How much does your song add with drums?<br>
<br>
Obviously you want to be over 200 with resists in both Magic and the Dragons breath weapon.  I think once you hit that plateau, you can start to balance your regular gear with your resist gear.  When we downed Trakanon, I was wearing my normal gear and with buffs, potions, and songs, I resisted almost everytime.<br>
<br>
If I had to list in order of importance the gear best suited for a bard on a dragon raid, I would say:<br>
<br>
Fire/Cold/Poison Resist<br>
Magic Resist<br>
AC<br>
HPs<br>
Fashion<br>
Stats<br>
<br>
This is pretty standard for anyone on a raid.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kalsyre Silverstring<br>
Ancient Bard of Brell   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/18/00 12:15:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> Interesting point Kalsyre, since I was referring to the Olde (and considerably weaker) dragons. Obviously you have bigger fish to fry and things may be slightly different with those dragons (not least that many of the later songs are vocal and you might as well use weapons if you've not got an instrument to play).<br>
<br>
I dunno about a fashion statement though... When it comes to the buff circle onwards, if my best resist gear looks like cloth, I'll wear it!<br>
<br>
I'm surprised that you say that bards are a luxury on raids though - maybe a luxury when it comes to resists, if everyone has such high resists vs Trakanon, but what about the attack buffs or debuffing? Please don't tell me we're expendable after 50th! <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/mastersofavalon" target="_blank">Masters of Avalon</a><br>
Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukalsyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalsyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/18/00 5:47:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> My comments are for any Dragon, Nag, Vox, Trak.  With just the right gear, potions, and spells, most anyone can get their resists up near 250.  This means you are not totally dependant on a bard for a high resist.<br>
<br>
However, a Bards resist is nice in that it always re-casts.  If you have your buffs dispelled, the Bard resist song always comes back.  Having a bard also means you dont need to substitute as much of your good gear for resist gear leaving you with higher AC, HPS, and Stats.<br>
<br>
As far as singing debuff songs on a raid I dont reccommed it.  I have tried that tactic on most of the gods and dragons in EQ and the high resist rate as well as the low debuff doesnt out weight the benefit of the added resist you can sing.<br>
<br>
Now I do reccommend VoV for dragon raids over guardian rythyms.  With a MM drum at level 50 you can do enough MR with elemental rythyms.  The added 20 AC, and 30 STR can really pay off for a tank group.<br>
<br>
As far as being expendable...thats pretty impossible.  Bards by design will always find someway to contribute.  We have too many songs and too many abilities to ever be expendable on any raid.  My point is, we arent a needed entity like a cleric.  We are a luxury.  Especially since there just are not many high level, well equipped, experienced Bards on Brell.<br>
<br>
Kalsyre Silverstring<br>
Ancient Bard of Brell<br>
<br>
<br>
p.s.  As a bard, you should &quot;Always&quot; be conscious of your attire.  People are always taking pictures before, during and after the fight, so you will want to look your best!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/18/00 10:37:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #2 - Dragons and what to wear</span><hr size=1> I'll look at the VoV thing when I get there - I've only just learnt how to sing Niv's...<br>
<br>
I guess as a Bard you could either go for the Aerosmith &quot;look is everything&quot; approach or the Nirvana &quot;who gives a f.ck&quot; approach... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
